summary: Code imports the Plots module, creates an array x from 0 to 10 and assigns sine values to y using . operator, but plot function is not called so no visualization happens. Finally, it prints out X_VALUES and Y_VALUES without any formatting.

details.content:
# using Plots
x=0:10;y=sin.(x);
# plot(x,y)
println("X_VALUES:")
println(x)
println()
println("Y_VALUES:")
